name: Mediterranean Frittata
author: sbmj
summary: I concocted this when I was trying to liven up an egg white frittata. It turned out deceptively decadent. The sun-dried tomatoes make all the difference.
ingredients: 1 (4.5 ounce) can sliced mushrooms with pieces, drained
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Place sun-dried tomatoes into a bowl of warm water until rehydrated, about 10 minutes
Heat olive oil in a small skillet over medium heat; cook and stir onion and garlic until onion is translucent, about 10 minutes
Add spinach; cook and stir until thawed and water is evaporated, about 5 minutes
Stir in mushrooms, sun-dried tomatoes, and feta cheese until well mixed
Whisk egg whites, skim milk, salt, pepper, and basil together in a bowl until very frothy
Carefully stir spinach mixture and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese into egg mixture
Pour into the prepared pan; top with remaining Parmesan cheese
Bake in the preheated oven until frittata is set and browned on top, about 25 minutes
